    "about": {
      "affiliations_heading": "Professional Affiliations",
      "awards_heading": "Awards & Honours",
      "bio": "Leonard Chan Tik Yuen, MH is a Hong Kong technology leader, entrepreneur, and public servant with over three decades of experience in the ICT industry. He is the Founder & CEO of tag.digital Limited, a technology consultancy focused on AI governance, cybersecurity, and digital strategy.\n\nLeonard holds numerous public appointments including Board Member of AIRDI, Deputy Chairman of HKIRC, and DevCom Chairman of TIA. He was awarded the Medal of Honour (MH) by the HKSAR Government in 2025 for distinguished public service.\n\nA double APICTA winner, UN World Summit Award laureate, and US patent holder, Leonard combines deep technical expertise with strategic vision for Hong Kong's digital future.",
